{"id":"cmmekzogz00011kf4gxzdfmgy","projectId":"cmmda4tdu00007oqcfk611gwg","campaignId":"cmmekujfn00012ihyp8y1mnei","type":"social_post","subtype":"feed_post","platform":"instagram","title":"Smart Scheduling for Ramadan","description":null,"status":"IN_REVIEW","currentVersion":1,"metadata":"{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"post_type\":\"infographic\",\"target_audience\":\"Clinic managers\",\"scheduled_time\":\"2026-03-10T18:00:00Z\",\"hashtags\":[\"SmartScheduling\",\"RamadanSchedule\",\"HealthcareEfficiency\",\"ZavisHealth\",\"ReduceNoShows\"],\"day\":4}","tags":null,"createdAt":"2026-03-06T07:36:44.963Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-06T07:46:27.599Z","versions":[{"id":"cmmekzoh100031kf4pjbv110q","assetId":"cmmekzogz00011kf4gxzdfmgy","version":1,"filePath":null,"content":"Your standard 9-to-5 schedule does not work during Ramadan. Here is why.\n\nPeak patient energy during fasting:\nMorning (8-11 AM): High energy, best for complex appointments\nAfternoon (2-5 PM): Lowest energy, reduce availability\nEvening (7-9 PM): Renewed energy post-Iftar\n\nClinics that adjust their scheduling during Ramadan see up to 35% fewer no-shows.\n\nZavis makes this effortless with AI-powered scheduling that adapts to your patients' needs.\n\n#SmartScheduling #RamadanSchedule #HealthcareEfficiency #ZavisHealth #ReduceNoShows #PatientEngagement #ClinicManagement #HealthTech #RamadanCare #AIHealthcare","metadata":"{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"post_type\":\"infographic\",\"target_audience\":\"Clinic managers\",\"scheduled_time\":\"2026-03-10T18:00:00Z\",\"hashtags\":[\"SmartScheduling\",\"RamadanSchedule\",\"HealthcareEfficiency\",\"ZavisHealth\",\"ReduceNoShows\"],\"day\":4}","changelog":"Initial generation","createdAt":"2026-03-06T07:36:44.965Z","feedbacks":[]}],"brandChecks":[{"id":"cmmelc61500014u0nh5a20ehj","assetId":"cmmekzogz00011kf4gxzdfmgy","versionNumber":1,"checkType":"visual_qa","score":90,"passed":true,"details":"{\"text_legibility\":95,\"brand_consistency\":92,\"visual_quality\":